Literals in C#

A literal is a fixed value that you assign directly to a variable in your program.
Example:

int age = 25;       // 25 is a literal
string name = "Ali"; // "Ali" is a literal

ðŸ“˜ Types of Literals
1. Integer Literals

Whole numbers

Default is int, but you can suffix:

L â†’ long

U â†’ unsigned

UL â†’ unsigned long

Example:

int x = 100;      // int
long y = 100L;    // long
uint z = 50U;     // unsigned int

2. Floating-Point Literals

Default is double, but you can suffix:

F â†’ float

M â†’ decimal

Example:

double d = 19.99;   // double by default
float f = 19.99F;   // float
decimal m = 19.99M; // decimal (high precision)

3. Character Literals

A single character inside single quotes 'A'

Can use escape sequences:

'\n' â†’ newline

'\t' â†’ tab

'\\' â†’ backslash

'\' â†’ single quote

Example:

char c1 = 'A';
char c2 = '\n'; // newline

4. String Literals

Sequence of characters inside double quotes "".

Use @ for verbatim string (ignores escape sequences).

Example:

string s1 = "Hello World";
string s2 = "C:\\Users\\Fagun";   // with escape
string s3 = @"C:\Users\Fagun";    // verbatim string

5. Boolean Literals

Only true or false.

bool isActive = true;

6. Null Literal

Represents no value.

string str = null;

ðŸ›  Example Program
using System;

namespace LiteralDemo
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            int num = 42;              // integer literal
            double pi = 3.14159;       // double literal
            float price = 9.99F;       // float literal
            char grade = 'A';          // char literal
            string path = @"C:\Data";  // string literal with verbatim
            bool isReady = true;       // boolean literal

            Console.WriteLine($"Number: {num}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Pi: {pi}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Price: {price}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Grade: {grade}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Path: {path}");
            Console.WriteLine($"Is Ready: {isReady}");
        }
    }
}
